{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"+1 Same result here.  This may be a result of Three.js changing the canvas size when you want to only change the renderer resolution:\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/5627\n\nIMO canvas should not be touched when making this call.\n","created_at":"2014-11-15T07:13:20.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-63163519","id":63163519,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDYzMTYzNTE5","updated_at":"2014-11-15T07:13:20.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/63163519","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3434843?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/erichlof","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MzQ4NDM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"erichlof","type":"User","id":3434843,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Then I guess it's a matter of updating the doc. \n","created_at":"2014-11-15T14:40:29.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-63174422","id":63174422,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDYzMTc0NDIy","updated_at":"2014-11-15T14:40:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/63174422","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars1.githubusercontent.com\/u\/2445163?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/jochasinga","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI0NDUxNjM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"jochasinga","type":"User","id":2445163,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/jochasinga\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Yea I found this odd too. I had to modify the canvas css to get the result I expected.\n","created_at":"2014-11-17T04:21:51.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-63258236","id":63258236,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDYzMjU4MjM2","updated_at":"2014-11-17T04:21:51.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/63258236","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/6549763?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/titansoftime","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjY1NDk3NjM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"titansoftime","type":"User","id":6549763,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/titansoftime\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Hi all,\nI found the source of the problem in WebGLRenderer.js.  Here's a link to the PR and issues:\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/5627\n\nTherefore, the Three.js 'getting started' example would need to look like this in order to function as intended by the OP:\n\n```\n    <script src=\"http:\/\/cdnjs.cloudflare.com\/ajax\/libs\/three.js\/r69\/three.min.js\"><\/script>\n    <script>\n        var scene = new THREE.Scene();\n        var camera = new THREE.PerspectiveCamera( 75, window.innerWidth\/window.innerHeight, 0.1, 1000 );\n\n        var renderer = new THREE.WebGLRenderer();\n        document.body.appendChild( renderer.domElement );\n\n        var width = window.innerWidth;\n        var height = window.innerHeight;\n\n        renderer.domElement.width = (width \/ 2) * renderer.devicePixelRatio;\n        renderer.domElement.height = (height \/ 2) * renderer.devicePixelRatio;\n        renderer.setViewport( 0, 0, (width \/ 2), (height \/ 2) );\n\n        var geometry = new THREE.BoxGeometry( 1, 1, 1 );\n        var material = new THREE.MeshBasicMaterial( { color: 0x00ff00 } );\n        var cube = new THREE.Mesh( geometry, material );\n        scene.add( cube );\n\n        camera.position.z = 5;\n\n        var render = function () {\n            requestAnimationFrame( render );\n\n            cube.rotation.x += 0.1;\n            cube.rotation.y += 0.1;\n\n            renderer.render(scene, camera);\n        };\n\n        render();\n```\n\nYou can try changing the '2's to '4's and notice how the image gets more pixelated and blurry.  If you change them to '1's, it runs at normal quality.\n\nThis shouldn't be too hard to fix inside the WebGLRender.setSize() method.\n","created_at":"2014-11-17T05:19:56.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-63261068","id":63261068,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDYzMjYxMDY4","updated_at":"2014-11-17T05:21:12.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/63261068","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3434843?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/erichlof","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MzQ4NDM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"erichlof","type":"User","id":3434843,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Hi again,\nTurns out the OP of the PR I linked to wants something different out of the WebGLRenderer.  Anyway, here is the problem for _this_ issue:\n\nWhen initially creating the WebGLRenderer, in line 43 the renderer.domElement is set equal to whatever the _canvas is.\n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/master\/src\/renderers\/WebGLRenderer.js#L43\n\nNow, all the pertinent info is stored in renderer.domElement, rather than _canvas.\nThen in lines 431 - 445, when the user calls renderer.setSize, it tries to change the _canvas variable, which is no longer relevant. Rather, it should change renderer.domElement, shouldn't it?\n\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/blob\/master\/src\/renderers\/WebGLRenderer.js#L431-L445\n\nEither that, or manually update everytime with:\n_canvas = this.domElement;\n","created_at":"2014-11-17T05:25:59.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-63261397","id":63261397,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDYzMjYxMzk3","updated_at":"2014-11-17T05:25:59.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/63261397","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/3434843?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/erichlof","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjM0MzQ4NDM=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"erichlof","type":"User","id":3434843,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/erichlof\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"The mentioned section of the \"Getting started\" tutorial is not valid anymore. If you want to retain a fullscreen canvas, set `width` and `height` of the canvas via CSS to `100%` and perform `.setSize()` like this:\r\n```javascript\r\nrenderer.setSize( window.innerWidth \/ 2, window.innerHeight \/ 2, false );\r\n```\r\nSetting `updateStyle` to `false` prevents any style changes to the canvas DOM element.\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/jsfiddle.net\/f2Lommf5\/842\/","created_at":"2018-01-23T14:59:34.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-359816676","id":359816676,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1OTgxNjY3Ng==","updated_at":"2018-01-23T15:00:38.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/359816676","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/12612165?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Mugen87","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEyNjEyMTY1","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Mugen87","type":"User","id":12612165,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Mugen87\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"OWNER","body":"Another option would be doing this:\r\n\r\n```js\r\nrenderer.setPixelRatio( window.devicePixelRatio \/ 2 );\r\n```","created_at":"2018-01-23T15:37:41.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631#issuecomment-359829226","id":359829226,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/5631","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM1OTgyOTIyNg==","updated_at":"2018-01-23T15:37:41.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/359829226","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/97088?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjk3MDg4","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"mrdoob","type":"User","id":97088,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/mrdoob\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"COLLABORA